<subSubSection id="41D67E80FFD5FF9CD6B6FEE8FDA0D58E" lastPageId="8" lastPageNumber="71" pageId="7" pageNumber="70" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="09732D0BFFD5FF93D6B6FEE8FC16D780" blockId="7.[151,1436,355,452]" pageId="7" pageNumber="70">
<emphasis id="3BB8F119FFD5FF93D6B6FEE8FEB6D73F" box="[151,273,355,380]" inLineHeading="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="70" reason="1">
<emphasis id="3BB8F119FFD5FF93D6B6FEE8FEADD738" bold="true" box="[151,266,355,380]" pageId="7" pageNumber="70">Diagnosis</emphasis>
.
</emphasis>
Scape, pedicel, legs and abdomen reddish-brown; thorax dark brown to black, opaque, densely grey pruinescent; scutum with four matte-black stripes in anterior view; tiny proepisternal setae; wing elongate, light brown; halter and both thoracic spiracles yellow; sternite 8 sclerotized.
</paragraph>
<caption id="5DB37D83FFD5FF93D6B6FA56FABCD00B" pageId="7" pageNumber="70" startId="7.[151,263,1501,1524]" targetBox="[265,1319,514,1474]" targetPageId="7">
<paragraph id="09732D0BFFD5FF93D6B6FA56FABCD00B" blockId="7.[151,1436,1501,1616]" pageId="7" pageNumber="70">
<emphasis id="3BB8F119FFD5FF93D6B6FA56FEF2D3B0" bold="true" box="[151,341,1501,1524]" pageId="7" pageNumber="70">FIGURES 32–40.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName id="CECC5688FFD5FF93D77DFA55FDC5D3B7" authority="Bezzi" authorityName="Bezzi" authorityYear="1909" box="[348,610,1501,1523]" class="Insecta" family="Empididae" genus="Empis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="70" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="leucostigma">
<emphasis id="3BB8F119FFD5FF93D77DFA55FDB9D3B7" box="[348,542,1501,1523]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="70">Empis leucostigma</emphasis>
Bezzi
</taxonomicName>
, holotype ♀. 
<emphasis id="3BB8F119FFD5FF93D4CEFA56FCAFD3B0" bold="true" box="[751,776,1501,1524]" pageId="7" pageNumber="70">32</emphasis>
, head, lateral view; 
<emphasis id="3BB8F119FFD5FF93D5FDFA56FC52D3B0" bold="true" box="[988,1013,1501,1524]" pageId="7" pageNumber="70">33</emphasis>
, occiput, frontal view; 
<emphasis id="3BB8F119FFD5FF93D2C9FA56FAA6D3B0" bold="true" box="[1256,1281,1501,1524]" pageId="7" pageNumber="70">34</emphasis>
, thorax, dorsal view; 
<emphasis id="3BB8F119FFD5FF93D6F6FA70FF57D056" bold="true" box="[215,240,1531,1554]" pageId="7" pageNumber="70">35</emphasis>
, left foreleg, posterior view; 
<emphasis id="3BB8F119FFD5FF93D405FA70FD9AD056" bold="true" box="[548,573,1531,1554]" pageId="7" pageNumber="70">36</emphasis>
, left midleg, posterior view; 
<emphasis id="3BB8F119FFD5FF93D54FFA70FC20D056" bold="true" box="[878,903,1531,1554]" pageId="7" pageNumber="70">37</emphasis>
, right hindleg, anterior view; 
<emphasis id="3BB8F119FFD5FF93D2E0FA70FB7DD056" bold="true" box="[1217,1242,1531,1554]" pageId="7" pageNumber="70">38</emphasis>
, termilalia (cercus broken), lateral view; 
<emphasis id="3BB8F119FFD5FF93D755F991FE2AD075" bold="true" box="[372,397,1562,1585]" pageId="7" pageNumber="70">39</emphasis>
, terminalia dorsal segments, dorsal view; 
<emphasis id="3BB8F119FFD5FF93D517F991FCE8D075" bold="true" box="[822,847,1562,1585]" pageId="7" pageNumber="70">40</emphasis>
, terminalia ventral segments, ventral view. Abbreviations: 
<emphasis id="3BB8F119FFD5FF93D6B6F9B2FF69D00A" bold="true" box="[151,206,1593,1616]" pageId="7" pageNumber="70">GF =</emphasis>
genital fork; 
<emphasis id="3BB8F119FFD5FF93D776F9B2FEC9D014" bold="true" box="[343,366,1593,1616]" pageId="7" pageNumber="70">St</emphasis>
= sternite; 
<emphasis id="3BB8F119FFD5FF93D7C1F9B2FE56D00A" bold="true" box="[480,497,1593,1614]" pageId="7" pageNumber="70">T</emphasis>
= tergites. Scales: Figures 
<emphasis id="3BB8F119FFD5FF93D523F9B2FCE6D014" bold="true" box="[770,833,1593,1616]" pageId="7" pageNumber="70">35–37</emphasis>
= 1.0 mm; 
<emphasis id="3BB8F119FFD5FF93D599F9B2FC50D014" bold="true" box="[952,1015,1593,1616]" pageId="7" pageNumber="70">32–34</emphasis>
= 0.5 mm; 
<emphasis id="3BB8F119FFD5FF93D24DF9B2FB0BD014" bold="true" box="[1132,1196,1593,1616]" pageId="7" pageNumber="70">38–40</emphasis>
