</paragraph>
</caption>
<paragraph id="09732D0BFFD5FF93D6E6F9F0FAF5D19C" blockId="7.[151,1436,1659,2008]" pageId="7" pageNumber="70">
<emphasis id="3BB8F119FFD5FF93D6E6F9F0FED0D0D0" bold="true" box="[199,375,1659,1684]" pageId="7" pageNumber="70">Re-description</emphasis>
. 
<typeStatus id="D67793A9FFD5FF93D7A9F9F7FE57D0D0" box="[392,496,1660,1684]" pageId="7" pageNumber="70">Holotype</typeStatus>
<emphasis id="3BB8F119FFD5FF93D7DBF9F0FDEED0D0" bold="true" box="[506,585,1659,1684]" pageId="7" pageNumber="70">female</emphasis>
. Body length 
<quantity id="CE3480EEFFD5FF93D4D3F9F7FCE9D0D7" box="[754,846,1660,1684]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="5.7" pageId="7" pageNumber="70" unit="mm" value="5.7">5.7 mm</quantity>
; wing length 
<quantity id="CE3480EEFFD5FF93D5CFF9F7FBEDD0D7" box="[1006,1098,1660,1684]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="6.6" pageId="7" pageNumber="70" unit="mm" value="6.6">6.6 mm</quantity>
. Dichoptic; frons black, grey pruinescent dorsally, grey-yellow ventrally, visible at certain angles, wider than ocellar tubercle, twice higher than wide, with 7 small, proclinate setae. Ocellar tubercle black, grey pruinescent. Ocellus glassy, yellow; with divergent anterior ocellar setae, 3 small posterior setae. Face bare, slightly higher than wide, slightly divergent towards proboscis, grey pruinescent, except ventrally, on protuberant part, with narrow shiny brown band. Postcranium (
<figureCitation id="91F7318EFFD5FF93D715F8BBFE20D10C" box="[308,391,1840,1864]" captionStart="FIGURES 32–40" captionStartId="7.[151,263,1501,1524]" captionTargetBox="[265,1319,514,1474]" captionTargetId="figure-332@7.[265,1323,505,1480]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURES 32–40. Empis leucostigma Bezzi, holotype ♀. 32, head, lateral view; 33, occiput, frontal view; 34, thorax, dorsal view; 35, left foreleg, posterior view; 36, left midleg, posterior view; 37, right hindleg, anterior view; 38, termilalia (cercus broken), lateral view; 39, terminalia dorsal segments, dorsal view; 40, terminalia ventral segments, ventral view. Abbreviations: GF = genital fork; St = sternite; T = tergites. Scales: Figures 35–37 = 1.0 mm; 32–34 = 0.5 mm; 38–40 = 0.2 mm." pageId="7" pageNumber="70">Fig. 32</figureCitation>
) dark brown to black, densely grey pruinescent; with uniserial to biserial postocular row of setae, superior ones longer (
<figureCitation id="91F7318EFFD5FF93D7F6F8DFFD8BD128" box="[471,556,1876,1900]" captionStart="FIGURES 32–40" captionStartId="7.[151,263,1501,1524]" captionTargetBox="[265,1319,514,1474]" captionTargetId="figure-332@7.[265,1323,505,1480]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURES 32–40. Empis leucostigma Bezzi, holotype ♀. 32, head, lateral view; 33, occiput, frontal view; 34, thorax, dorsal view; 35, left foreleg, posterior view; 36, left midleg, posterior view; 37, right hindleg, anterior view; 38, termilalia (cercus broken), lateral view; 39, terminalia dorsal segments, dorsal view; 40, terminalia ventral segments, ventral view. Abbreviations: GF = genital fork; St = sternite; T = tergites. Scales: Figures 35–37 = 1.0 mm; 32–34 = 0.5 mm; 38–40 = 0.2 mm." pageId="7" pageNumber="70">Fig. 33</figureCitation>
); occipital setae restricted to dorsal half, misaligned. Gena with slender setae and postgena with shorter setae. Antenna (
<figureCitation id="91F7318EFFD5FF93D4AAF8F3FD47D1D4" box="[651,736,1912,1936]" captionStart="FIGURES 32–40" captionStartId="7.[151,263,1501,1524]" captionTargetBox="[265,1319,514,1474]" captionTargetId="figure-332@7.[265,1323,505,1480]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURES 32–40. Empis leucostigma Bezzi, holotype ♀. 32, head, lateral view; 33, occiput, frontal view; 34, thorax, dorsal view; 35, left foreleg, posterior view; 36, left midleg, posterior view; 37, right hindleg, anterior view; 38, termilalia (cercus broken), lateral view; 39, terminalia dorsal segments, dorsal view; 40, terminalia ventral segments, ventral view. Abbreviations: GF = genital fork; St = sternite; T = tergites. Scales: Figures 35–37 = 1.0 mm; 32–34 = 0.5 mm; 38–40 = 0.2 mm." pageId="7" pageNumber="70">Fig. 32</figureCitation>
) with scape and pedicel reddish-brown; postpedicel velvety matte-black, coniform, 1.5X longer than scape and pedicel together, twice as long as stylus. Proboscis (
<figureCitation id="91F7318EFFD5FF93D361F817FA34D1F0" box="[1344,1427,1948,1972]" captionStart="FIGURES 32–40" captionStartId="7.[151,263,1501,1524]" captionTargetBox="[265,1319,514,1474]" captionTargetId="figure-332@7.[265,1323,505,1480]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURES 32–40. Empis leucostigma Bezzi, holotype ♀. 32, head, lateral view; 33, occiput, frontal view; 34, thorax, dorsal view; 35, left foreleg, posterior view; 36, left midleg, posterior view; 37, right hindleg, anterior view; 38, termilalia (cercus broken), lateral view; 39, terminalia dorsal segments, dorsal view; 40, terminalia ventral segments, ventral view. Abbreviations: GF = genital fork; St = sternite; T = tergites. Scales: Figures 35–37 = 1.0 mm; 32–34 = 0.5 mm; 38–40 = 0.2 mm." pageId="7" pageNumber="70">Fig. 32</figureCitation>
) about 2.5X longer than head; labrum yellow, shiny; labium brown. Palpus brown with distinct slender setae.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="09732D0BFFDAFF9CD6E6FF1CFBD8D7B0" blockId="8.[151,1436,151,1259]" pageId="8" pageNumber="71">
Thorax (
<figureCitation id="91F7318EFFDAFF9CD708FF1CFED9D6EB" box="[297,382,151,175]" captionStart="FIGURES 32–40" captionStartId="7.[151,263,1501,1524]" captionTargetBox="[265,1319,514,1474]" captionTargetId="figure-332@7.[265,1323,505,1480]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURES 32–40. Empis leucostigma Bezzi, holotype ♀. 32, head, lateral view; 33, occiput, frontal view; 34, thorax, dorsal view; 35, left foreleg, posterior view; 36, left midleg, posterior view; 37, right hindleg, anterior view; 38, termilalia (cercus broken), lateral view; 39, terminalia dorsal segments, dorsal view; 40, terminalia ventral segments, ventral view. Abbreviations: GF = genital fork; St = sternite; T = tergites. Scales: Figures 35–37 = 1.0 mm; 32–34 = 0.5 mm; 38–40 = 0.2 mm." pageId="8" pageNumber="71">Fig. 34</figureCitation>
) dark brown to black, densely grey pruinescent. Scutum, in anterior view, with four matteblack stripes; two paramedian stripes, between acrostichal and dorsocentral rows, narrower and extending slightly beyond transverse suture; two lateral stripes between dorsocentral and supra-alar rows, extending from postpronotal lobe to level of postalar callus. Anterior and posterior spiracles yellow. Chaetotaxy: antepronotum with 1 robust and various small apparently biserials; 1 robust, 4–5 weak postpronotals; 2–3 proepisternals; roughly 15 small and slender proepimerals; roughly 10 uniserial acrostichals, slightly out of alignment; roughly 10 biserial dorsocentrals, posteriormost seta longest and more robust; 1 presutural intra-alar; 2 small postsutural intra-alars just posterior to transverse suture and 1 posterior; 4 small aligned presutural supra-alar; 4 postsutural supra-alars, posteriormost seta robust; 1 robust and 1 weak postalars; 3 robust posterior and 8 weak anterior notopleurals; 4 scutellars, shorter basal and subapical pairs intermixed with longer; 15–17 laterotergitals.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="09732D0BFFDAFF9CD6E6FD8BFC24D41B" blockId="8.[151,1436,151,1259]" pageId="8" pageNumber="71">
Legs (
<figureCitation id="91F7318EFFDAFF9CD72CFE74FE29D453" box="[269,398,511,535]" captionStart="FIGURES 32–40" captionStartId="7.[151,263,1501,1524]" captionTargetBox="[265,1319,514,1474]" captionTargetId="figure-332@7.[265,1323,505,1480]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURES 32–40. Empis leucostigma Bezzi, holotype ♀. 32, head, lateral view; 33, occiput, frontal view; 34, thorax, dorsal view; 35, left foreleg, posterior view; 36, left midleg, posterior view; 37, right hindleg, anterior view; 38, termilalia (cercus broken), lateral view; 39, terminalia dorsal segments, dorsal view; 40, terminalia ventral segments, ventral view. Abbreviations: GF = genital fork; St = sternite; T = tergites. Scales: Figures 35–37 = 1.0 mm; 32–34 = 0.5 mm; 38–40 = 0.2 mm." pageId="8" pageNumber="71">Figs 35–37</figureCitation>
) reddish-brown, grey pruinescent; all legs with some setae slightly longer than background setae, especially on antero- and posterodorsal rows, and apical antero- and posteroventral setae of tibiae and tarsomeres; hind coxa thicker and shorter than both anterior coxae.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="09732D0BFFDAFF9CD6E6FDE7FB38D4E3" blockId="8.[151,1436,151,1259]" pageId="8" pageNumber="71">
Wing (
<figureCitation id="91F7318EFFDAFF9CD737FDE7FECFD4C0" box="[278,360,620,644]" captionStart="FIGURES 78–85" captionStartId="15.[151,263,962,985]" captionTargetBox="[306,1281,194,941]" captionTargetId="figure-441@15.[306,1281,193,941]" captionTargetPageId="15" captionText="FIGURES 78–85. Wings. 78, Empis angustipennis Bezzi, lectotype ♀; 79, E. chiragra Bezzi, lectotype ♂; 80, E. induta Bezzi, female holotype; 81, E. leucostigma Bezzi, holotype ♀. 82, E. liodes Bezzi, holotype ♀. 83, E. lucidilabris Bezzi, ♀ from Peru; 84, E. penniventris Bezzi, holotype ♀. 85, E. spinifera Bezzi, lectotype ♂. Length of each wing informed along the text." pageId="8" pageNumber="71">Fig. 81</figureCitation>
) elongate, light brown, pterostigma brown, veins dark brown; base of costal vein with robust seta (not represented in figure). Vein R 
<subScript id="95482F4EFFDAFF9CD468FD14FDF6D4E9" attach="left" box="[585,593,671,685]" fontSize="6" pageId="8" pageNumber="71">1</subScript>
bare above, not dilated towards apex. Halter yellow.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="09732D0BFFDAFF9CD6E6FD3CFE1ED553" blockId="8.[151,1436,151,1259]" pageId="8" pageNumber="71">Abdomen reddish-brown, subshiny, grey pruinescent, with pruinescence restricted to posterior margin of tergites when viewed from posterior angle; tergites with marginal setae slightly shorter than laterals. Sternites concolorous with tergites.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="09732D0BFFDAFF9CD6E6FCA9FB01D5C6" blockId="8.[151,1436,151,1259]" pageId="8" pageNumber="71">
Terminalia. Tergite 8 shorter than respective sternite (
<figureCitation id="91F7318EFFDAFF9CD500FCA9FCD2D57E" box="[801,885,802,826]" captionStart="FIGURES 32–40" captionStartId="7.[151,263,1501,1524]" captionTargetBox="[265,1319,514,1474]" captionTargetId="figure-332@7.[265,1323,505,1480]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURES 32–40. Empis leucostigma Bezzi, holotype ♀. 32, head, lateral view; 33, occiput, frontal view; 34, thorax, dorsal view; 35, left foreleg, posterior view; 36, left midleg, posterior view; 37, right hindleg, anterior view; 38, termilalia (cercus broken), lateral view; 39, terminalia dorsal segments, dorsal view; 40, terminalia ventral segments, ventral view. Abbreviations: GF = genital fork; St = sternite; T = tergites. Scales: Figures 35–37 = 1.0 mm; 32–34 = 0.5 mm; 38–40 = 0.2 mm." pageId="8" pageNumber="71">Fig. 38</figureCitation>
); sternite slightly acute, sclerotized medially and apically, with small clear central circle (
<figureCitation id="91F7318EFFDAFF9CD47BFCCCFD08D51B" box="[602,687,839,863]" captionStart="FIGURES 32–40" captionStartId="7.[151,263,1501,1524]" captionTargetBox="[265,1319,514,1474]" captionTargetId="figure-332@7.[265,1323,505,1480]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURES 32–40. Empis leucostigma Bezzi, holotype ♀. 32, head, lateral view; 33, occiput, frontal view; 34, thorax, dorsal view; 35, left foreleg, posterior view; 36, left midleg, posterior view; 37, right hindleg, anterior view; 38, termilalia (cercus broken), lateral view; 39, terminalia dorsal segments, dorsal view; 40, terminalia ventral segments, ventral view. Abbreviations: GF = genital fork; St = sternite; T = tergites. Scales: Figures 35–37 = 1.0 mm; 32–34 = 0.5 mm; 38–40 = 0.2 mm." pageId="8" pageNumber="71">Fig. 40</figureCitation>
). Tergite 10 with deep basal sinus (
<figureCitation id="91F7318EFFDAFF9CD21FFCCCFB37D51B" box="[1086,1168,839,863]" captionStart="FIGURES 32–40" captionStartId="7.[151,263,1501,1524]" captionTargetBox="[265,1319,514,1474]" captionTargetId="figure-332@7.[265,1323,505,1480]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURES 32–40. Empis leucostigma Bezzi, holotype ♀. 32, head, lateral view; 33, occiput, frontal view; 34, thorax, dorsal view; 35, left foreleg, posterior view; 36, left midleg, posterior view; 37, right hindleg, anterior view; 38, termilalia (cercus broken), lateral view; 39, terminalia dorsal segments, dorsal view; 40, terminalia ventral segments, ventral view. Abbreviations: GF = genital fork; St = sternite; T = tergites. Scales: Figures 35–37 = 1.0 mm; 32–34 = 0.5 mm; 38–40 = 0.2 mm." pageId="8" pageNumber="71">Fig. 39</figureCitation>
) and respective sternite with shallow basal sinus (
<figureCitation id="91F7318EFFDAFF9CD796FCE1FDABD5C6" box="[439,524,874,898]" captionStart="FIGURES 32–40" captionStartId="7.[151,263,1501,1524]" captionTargetBox="[265,1319,514,1474]" captionTargetId="figure-332@7.[265,1323,505,1480]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURES 32–40. Empis leucostigma Bezzi, holotype ♀. 32, head, lateral view; 33, occiput, frontal view; 34, thorax, dorsal view; 35, left foreleg, posterior view; 36, left midleg, posterior view; 37, right hindleg, anterior view; 38, termilalia (cercus broken), lateral view; 39, terminalia dorsal segments, dorsal view; 40, terminalia ventral segments, ventral view. Abbreviations: GF = genital fork; St = sternite; T = tergites. Scales: Figures 35–37 = 1.0 mm; 32–34 = 0.5 mm; 38–40 = 0.2 mm." pageId="8" pageNumber="71">Fig. 40</figureCitation>
); genital fork with arms U-shaped (
<figureCitation id="91F7318EFFDAFF9CD5B8FCE1FC49D5C6" box="[921,1006,874,898]" captionStart="FIGURES 32–40" captionStartId="7.[151,263,1501,1524]" captionTargetBox="[265,1319,514,1474]" captionTargetId="figure-332@7.[265,1323,505,1480]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURES 32–40. Empis leucostigma Bezzi, holotype ♀. 32, head, lateral view; 33, occiput, frontal view; 34, thorax, dorsal view; 35, left foreleg, posterior view; 36, left midleg, posterior view; 37, right hindleg, anterior view; 38, termilalia (cercus broken), lateral view; 39, terminalia dorsal segments, dorsal view; 40, terminalia ventral segments, ventral view. Abbreviations: GF = genital fork; St = sternite; T = tergites. Scales: Figures 35–37 = 1.0 mm; 32–34 = 0.5 mm; 38–40 = 0.2 mm." pageId="8" pageNumber="71">Fig. 39</figureCitation>
); cercus broken.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="09732D0BFFDAFF9CD6E6FC04FE2FD5E3" blockId="8.[151,1436,151,1259]" box="[199,392,911,935]" pageId="8" pageNumber="71">
