<subSubSection id="41D67E80FFDAFF9CD6E6FBC9FC42D2AE" pageId="8" pageNumber="71" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="09732D0BFFDAFF9CD6E6FBC9FC42D2AE" blockId="8.[151,1436,151,1259]" pageId="8" pageNumber="71">
<emphasis id="3BB8F119FFDAFF9CD6E6FBC9FEEBD21E" box="[199,332,1090,1115]" inLineHeading="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="71" reason="1">
<emphasis id="3BB8F119FFDAFF9CD6E6FBC9FEE2D21F" bold="true" box="[199,325,1090,1115]" pageId="8" pageNumber="71">Discussion</emphasis>
.
</emphasis>
The female specimen of 
<taxonomicName id="CECC5688FFDAFF9CD456FBC8FC87D21F" authorityName="Bezzi" authorityYear="1909" box="[631,800,1091,1115]" class="Insecta" family="Empididae" genus="Empis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="71" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="leucostigma">
<emphasis id="3BB8F119FFDAFF9CD456FBC8FC87D21F" box="[631,800,1091,1115]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="71">E. leucostigma</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is identified as part of group II in 
<bibRefCitation id="6D5D50FAFFDAFF9CD29DFBC9FACED21E" author="Collin, J. E." box="[1212,1385,1090,1114]" pageId="8" pageNumber="71" refId="ref11039" refString="Collin, J. E. (1933) Empididae. Diptera of Patagonia and South Chile. Volume 4, London, British Museum of Natural History, London. Vol. 4, 334 pp., 74 figs." type="book" year="1933">Collin’s (1933)</bibRefCitation>
key through the same couplets presented above for 
<taxonomicName id="CECC5688FFDAFF9CD497FBE3FCD4D23B" authorityName="Bezzi" authorityYear="1909" box="[694,883,1128,1151]" class="Insecta" family="Empididae" genus="Empis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="71" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="angustipennis">
<emphasis id="3BB8F119FFDAFF9CD497FBE3FCD4D23B" box="[694,883,1128,1151]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="71">E. angustipennis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. Further in the key it ends in couplet (15) of 
<taxonomicName id="CECC5688FFDAFF9CD3A5FBE3FE32D2E6" authority="Bigot, 1857" authorityName="Bigot" authorityYear="1857" class="Insecta" family="Empididae" genus="Empis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="71" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="variabilis">
<emphasis id="3BB8F119FFDAFF9CD3A5FBE3FEA5D2E7" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="71">E. variabilis</emphasis>
Bigot, 1857
</taxonomicName>
due to “thorax with four contrasting dark stripes”. They are not conspecific because 
<taxonomicName id="CECC5688FFDAFF9CD3A5FB00FEB9D283" authorityName="Bezzi" authorityYear="1909" class="Insecta" family="Empididae" genus="Empis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="71" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="leucostigma">
<emphasis id="3BB8F119FFDAFF9CD3A5FB00FEB9D283" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="71">E. leucostigma</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has three stripes and a reddish-brown abdomen (yellow at apex in 
<taxonomicName id="CECC5688FFDAFF9CD23FFB3BFB0DD283" authorityName="Bigot" authorityYear="1857" box="[1054,1194,1199,1223]" class="Insecta" family="Empididae" genus="Empis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="71" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="variabilis">
<emphasis id="3BB8F119FFDAFF9CD23FFB3BFB0DD283" box="[1054,1194,1199,1223]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="71">E. variabilis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
), a light brown wing (almost hyaline in 
<taxonomicName id="CECC5688FFDAFF9CD749FB58FE55D2AF" authorityName="Bigot" authorityYear="1857" box="[360,498,1235,1259]" class="Insecta" family="Empididae" genus="Empis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="71" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="variabilis">
<emphasis id="3BB8F119FFDAFF9CD749FB58FE55D2AF" box="[360,498,1235,1259]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="71">E. variabilis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
), and 4 scutellar setae (
<quantity id="CE3480EEFFDAFF9CD4DAFB59FCE4D2AE" box="[763,835,1234,1258]" metricMagnitude="-1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.778" metricValueMax="2.032" metricValueMin="1.524" pageId="8" pageNumber="71" unit="in" value="7.0" valueMax="8.0" valueMin="6.0">6–8 in</quantity>
<taxonomicName id="CECC5688FFDAFF9CD56BFB58FC73D2AF" authorityName="Bigot" authorityYear="1857" box="[842,980,1235,1259]" class="Insecta" family="Empididae" genus="Empis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="71" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="variabilis">
<emphasis id="3BB8F119FFDAFF9CD56BFB58FC73D2AF" box="[842,980,1235,1259]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="71">E. variabilis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
